&lt;h1&gt;Images Representation&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Use Pre-trained CNN to generate activation maps&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deep convolutional neural network can output the activation map, which are features representing the content or style of an image. In this project, a ImageNet pretrained vgg16 network will be used to output the feature at different layers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VGG 16 is a deep CNN including 5 convolutional layers, 2 fully connetced layers and 1 softmax output layer. In this project, only the convolutional layers will be used as they will output the activation maps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The architecture of VGG16 is on the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; &quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/db1c097ad63b388bcd303d0a65fee384/5a190/vgg16.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 23.64864864864865%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        alt=&quot;vgg16&quot;
        title=&quot;vgg16&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/db1c097ad63b388bcd303d0a65fee384/fcda8/vgg16.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/db1c097ad63b388bcd303d0a65fee384/12f09/vgg16.png 148w,
/static/db1c097ad63b388bcd303d0a65fee384/e4a3f/vgg16.png 295w,
/static/db1c097ad63b388bcd303d0a65fee384/fcda8/vgg16.png 590w,
/static/db1c097ad63b388bcd303d0a65fee384/5a190/vgg16.png 800w&quot;
        sizes=&quot;(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px&quot;
        style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;&quot;
        loading=&quot;lazy&quot;
      /&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VGG16 takes 224 as the input size and all the convolutional layers are hidden layers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; &quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/3d3d1764d8e9bbff8810f2631bc8ff58/2e237/layer2.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 48.64864864864865%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        alt=&quot;layer2&quot;
        title=&quot;layer2&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/3d3d1764d8e9bbff8810f2631bc8ff58/fcda8/layer2.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/3d3d1764d8e9bbff8810f2631bc8ff58/12f09/layer2.png 148w,
/static/3d3d1764d8e9bbff8810f2631bc8ff58/e4a3f/layer2.png 295w,
/static/3d3d1764d8e9bbff8810f2631bc8ff58/fcda8/layer2.png 590w,
/static/3d3d1764d8e9bbff8810f2631bc8ff58/2e237/layer2.png 790w&quot;
        sizes=&quot;(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px&quot;
        style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;&quot;
        loading=&quot;lazy&quot;
      /&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Layer 2 of the CNN. The left image represents what the CNN has learned and the right image has parts of actual images.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In layer 2 of the CNN the model is already picking up more interesting shapes than just diagonal lines. In the sixth square (counting horizontally) you can see that the model is picking up circular shapes. Also, the last square is looking at corners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; &quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/f9dcb43e3297f438b3c71729c2a96d5a/5a190/layer3.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 37.16216216216216%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        alt=&quot;layer3&quot;
        title=&quot;layer3&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/f9dcb43e3297f438b3c71729c2a96d5a/fcda8/layer3.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/f9dcb43e3297f438b3c71729c2a96d5a/12f09/layer3.png 148w,
/static/f9dcb43e3297f438b3c71729c2a96d5a/e4a3f/layer3.png 295w,
/static/f9dcb43e3297f438b3c71729c2a96d5a/fcda8/layer3.png 590w,
/static/f9dcb43e3297f438b3c71729c2a96d5a/5a190/layer3.png 800w&quot;
        sizes=&quot;(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px&quot;
        style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;&quot;
        loading=&quot;lazy&quot;
      /&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In layer 3 we can see that the model is starting to learn more specific things. The first square shows that the model is now able to recognize geometrical patterns. The sixth square is recognizing car tires. And the eleventh square is recognizing people.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; &quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/538599044d8f9033312285511b290641/00d43/layer5.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 24.324324324324326%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        alt=&quot;layer5&quot;
        title=&quot;layer5&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/538599044d8f9033312285511b290641/fcda8/layer5.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/538599044d8f9033312285511b290641/12f09/layer5.png 148w,
/static/538599044d8f9033312285511b290641/e4a3f/layer5.png 295w,
/static/538599044d8f9033312285511b290641/fcda8/layer5.png 590w,
/static/538599044d8f9033312285511b290641/efc66/layer5.png 885w,
/static/538599044d8f9033312285511b290641/00d43/layer5.png 1000w&quot;
        sizes=&quot;(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px&quot;
        style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;&quot;
        loading=&quot;lazy&quot;
      /&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Finally, layers 4 and 5 continue this trend. Layer 5 is picking up tings that are very useful for our dogs and cats problem. It is also recognizing unicycles and bird/reptile eyes. Be aware that these images only show a very small fraction of things learned by each layer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the network went deeper, the features became more high-level and abstrated for human to recongnize. The pretrained vgg16 will be able to filter out the objects in one image.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Representation of Content&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; &quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/d20eef1a53fd3fa204018097dd48d381/bca35/rep_content.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 79.05405405405406%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        alt=&quot;rep content&quot;
        title=&quot;rep content&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/d20eef1a53fd3fa204018097dd48d381/fcda8/rep_content.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/d20eef1a53fd3fa204018097dd48d381/12f09/rep_content.png 148w,
/static/d20eef1a53fd3fa204018097dd48d381/e4a3f/rep_content.png 295w,
/static/d20eef1a53fd3fa204018097dd48d381/fcda8/rep_content.png 590w,
/static/d20eef1a53fd3fa204018097dd48d381/bca35/rep_content.png 683w&quot;
