&lt;p&gt;Similarly, the style of one image could also be extratced using the same method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Feature and Gram Matrix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The activation map is a combined matrix which are high-level features human can easily recongnize.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In style transfer, network need to convert them into another shape for the traning and testing procedure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First, convert the activation map into feature matirx.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 475px; &quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/3d1d42e258bf0bcd10b07e2b626101b9/466da/feature_matrix.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 55.4054054054054%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        alt=&quot;feature matrix&quot;
        title=&quot;feature matrix&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/3d1d42e258bf0bcd10b07e2b626101b9/466da/feature_matrix.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/3d1d42e258bf0bcd10b07e2b626101b9/12f09/feature_matrix.png 148w,
/static/3d1d42e258bf0bcd10b07e2b626101b9/e4a3f/feature_matrix.png 295w,
/static/3d1d42e258bf0bcd10b07e2b626101b9/466da/feature_matrix.png 475w&quot;
        sizes=&quot;(max-width: 475px) 100vw, 475px&quot;
        style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;&quot;
        loading=&quot;lazy&quot;
      /&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each row of feature matrix represents different features, each column represent each pixel in activation map.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The feature matrix contains all the inforamtion in style image.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Another information needs to be known is the relationship between different features. The inner product of the feature matrix could describe the relationship in a clear manner. The new matrix is named as gram matrix.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In python, the gram matrix could be easily calculated (F is feature matrix):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;text&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;def Gram(F):
    return np.dot(F.T, F) / F.size&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The gram matrix is illustrated on the following. Each element in the gram matrix will represent 2 features on the row and column respectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 424px; &quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/e6590ccc3dbb0c50055b3e011f261194/1cfa9/gram_matrix.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        alt=&quot;gram matrix&quot;
        title=&quot;gram matrix&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/e6590ccc3dbb0c50055b3e011f261194/1cfa9/gram_matrix.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/e6590ccc3dbb0c50055b3e011f261194/12f09/gram_matrix.png 148w,
/static/e6590ccc3dbb0c50055b3e011f261194/e4a3f/gram_matrix.png 295w,
/static/e6590ccc3dbb0c50055b3e011f261194/1cfa9/gram_matrix.png 424w&quot;
        sizes=&quot;(max-width: 424px) 100vw, 424px&quot;
        style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;&quot;
        loading=&quot;lazy&quot;
      /&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If one element on the gram matrix is large, the relation between these 2 features will be stronger. For example, in one cell, the row represent the tree, the column is flower, the value is larger means this artist prefers the combination of tree and flower.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The size of gram matrix is only determined by the number of feature map. In style transfer, the input size is not strictly defined.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Training Progress&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The whole process is showed on the following.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; &quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/da2ff99480227e9353883c1846687931/e4611/style_transfer_sketch.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 127.02702702702702%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        alt=&quot;style transfer sketch&quot;
        title=&quot;style transfer sketch&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/da2ff99480227e9353883c1846687931/fcda8/style_transfer_sketch.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/da2ff99480227e9353883c1846687931/12f09/style_transfer_sketch.png 148w,
/static/da2ff99480227e9353883c1846687931/e4a3f/style_transfer_sketch.png 295w,
/static/da2ff99480227e9353883c1846687931/fcda8/style_transfer_sketch.png 590w,
/static/da2ff99480227e9353883c1846687931/efc66/style_transfer_sketch.png 885w,
/static/da2ff99480227e9353883c1846687931/c83ae/style_transfer_sketch.png 1180w,
/static/da2ff99480227e9353883c1846687931/e4611/style_transfer_sketch.png 1298w&quot;
        sizes=&quot;(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px&quot;
        style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;&quot;
        loading=&quot;lazy&quot;
      /&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the forward propagation, input the style image and content image into the network, extracted the feature.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For each the content image, the content loss is determined as the the sum of all the training images.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The cost function is the sum of the style loss and content loss.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the forward propagation, compute the gradient of total loss over the content image. Take the gradient descent until total loss converges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The content loss is a determined value defined by the training images.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Minimize the loss&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The calculation equation of the style loss and content loss is actually the equation of mean square function (MSE).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;MSE Equation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the training the loss will be the Mean Square Error (MSE) equation. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; &quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/5832a13becfbaed8bbd194efe7dc89f4/9100a/mse.jpg&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 39.86486486486486%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
